Having been hunting with groups of druid and other classes who can charm lately, I've noticed how difficult it can be to determine which mob is a pet and which one we are killing.  Especially when you are fighting in a zone like ME, with 3 charmed wolves and a wolf you are killing.  Talk about confusion!  Even trying to use the F-keys and /assist to target can be a challenge. 

I would love to see a modification made that would make it easier to see when an animal has been charmed as a pet.  Maybe a different color on it's name?  Or a star or some kind of indication that it is a charmed pet.  Any other ideas or comments?  Has anyone else had this same problem?

Just my 2cp, would certainly make things a bit less confusing.

